-- Stanford’s Bid to Delay Fraud Trial Denied
-- B y   L a u r e l   B r u b a k e r   C a l k i n s
-- 2011-12-28T21:42:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/stanford-s-bid-to-delay-fraud-trial-denied.html
R. Allen Stanford’s request for more
time to prepare to face charges he led a $7 billion investment
fraud scheme was denied by the judge who declared him mentally
fit for trial. Jury selection will begin in Houston federal
court on Jan. 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
